#Antiasthmatic
Epinephrine/adrenaline: anaphylaxis, cardiac arrest
Budesonide (Pulmicort)
Montelukast (Singulair)
Salbutamol (Albuterol, Ventolin): bronchodilator, β2-adrenergic agonist, short-term
Tiotropium (Spiriva): bronchodilator, muscarinic antagonist, long-term

#Analgesic: pain relievers
Non-opioid
- Paracetamol (Panadol): common, antipyretic (overdose ~5g: liver failure)
- Ibuprofen (Nurofen): common, anti-inflammatory
- Aspirin: common, anti-inflammatory (overdose ~10g: brain/lungs edema)
- Naproxen (Aleve): anti-inflammatory
Opioid: μ-opioid agonist
- Morphine: recreational drug, found in opium, addictive
- Codeine: prodrug of morphine, found in opium
- Heroin: recreational drug, addictive
- Fentanyl: very strong, addictive
- Methadone: relieves opioid withdrawal

#Anesthetic: block nerve receptors, unconsciousness when general
General via inhalation
- Nitrous oxide
- Isoflurane
- Halothane
- Sevoflurane
General
- Ketamine: NMDA antagonist
- Propofol: intravenous
- Thiopental: intravenous
Local: blocks sodium channels on neuron membrane
- Lidocaine
- Benzocaine
- Bupivacaine

