#Cardiovascular system
=Antianginal
Nitroglycerin / Glyceryl trinitrate: vasodilator, sublingual
Isosorbide dinitrate: vasodilator, oral
Nifedipine: calcium channel blocker, oral
=Antiarrhythmic
Amiodarone: potassium channel blocker, contains iodine, oral, accumulates in body, serious side effects
Lidocaine: sodium channel blocker, intravenous
Verapamil: calcium channel blocker, oral, not with beta blockers
=Cardiac glycoside: sodium-potassium pump inhibitor, steroid code, increase output, decrease heart rate
Digoxin / Digitalis: foxglove plant, excretion by kidney
Digitoxin: foxglove plant
=Hypolipidemic: prevent cardiovascular diseases
Statins: HMGCR inhibitor, increase LDL receptors in liver
- Simvastatin: common
- Atorvastatin: common
- Rosuvastatin: common
- Fluvastatin
- Lovastatin
- Pravastatin
=Diuretic
Thiazides: inhibit Na-Cl cotransporter, hypokalemia
- Hydrochlorothiazide: common
- Indapamide
- Chlortalidone
Loop diuretic: inhibit Na-K-Cl cotransporter
- Furosemide: common
- Torasemide
Potassium sparing: with thiazides
- Amiloride: sodium channel blocker, oral
- Triamterene: sodium channel blocker, oral
- Spironolactone: aldosterone antagonist (affects testosterone)
- Eplerenone: aldosterone antagonist
Acetazolamide: carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, oral, mild acidosis, treat glaucoma and epilepsy
Mannitol: osmotic (inhibits reabsorption), intravenous, heart failure risk

=vasopressin agonist, antidiuretic, increase blood pressure
Desmopressin
Terlipressin

=Tocolytic: suppress contractions
=Uterotonic: induce contractions
Oxytocin

=Erythropoietin: treat anemia due to kidney disease
Darbepoetin: longer life-time
Epoetin

=Mineral supplements
Calcium gluconate: protect heart from hyperkalemia

